000100*****************************************************************         
000200**                                                                        
000300**   Use DISPLAY statements to print out a formatted XML message.         
000400**   This routine is used to aid in debugging the XML PARSE               
000500**   and XML GENERATE commands in a COBOL program by formatting           
000600**   an XML message into a more readable format.                          
000700**                                                                        
000800**   This copybook is used in conjunction with ISPD008.                   
000900**   Your program must also include copybooks ISWS007 & ISPD007.          
001000**                                                                        
001100*****************************************************************         
001200                                                                          
001300* Fill in this field and PERFORM 9555-DISPLAY-FORMATTED-XML.              
001410 01  XML-UNFORMATTED-MSG         PIC X(999999)   VALUE SPACES.            
001500                                                                          
001510 01  XML-FORMATTED-LINES          PIC 99999      VALUE ZERO.              
001520 01  XML-FORMATTED-MESSAGE.                                               
001530     05  XML-FMT-MSG              PIC X(120)                              
001540         OCCURS 0 TO 99999 TIMES                                          
001550         DEPENDING ON XML-FORMATTED-LINES.                                
001560                                                                          
001600 01  XML-VARIABLES.                                                       
001700     05  XML-DOCUMENT-SW         PIC X           VALUE 'N'.               
001800         88  XML-DOCUMENT-START                  VALUE 'Y'.               
001900         88  XML-DOCUMENT-RESET                  VALUE 'N'.               
002000     05  XML-ELEMENT-SW          PIC X           VALUE 'C'.               
002100         88  XML-ELEMENT-OPEN                    VALUE 'O'.               
002200         88  XML-ELEMENT-CLOSED                  VALUE 'C'.               
002300     05  XML-CONTENT-SW          PIC X           VALUE 'N'.               
002400         88  XML-HAS-CONTENT                     VALUE 'Y'.               
002500         88  XML-NO-CONTENT                      VALUE 'N'.               
002600                                                                          
002700     05  XML-INDENT              PIC X(60)       VALUE SPACES.            
002800     05  XML-DEPTH               PIC 9(03)       VALUE ZERO.              
002900     05  XML-BUFFER              PIC X(120)      VALUE SPACES.            
003000     05  XML-POS                 PIC 9(03)       VALUE 1.                 
003010     05  XML-LATEST-ELEMENT      PIC X(120)      VALUE SPACES.            
003020     05  XML-LATEST-LENGTH       PIC 9(03)       VALUE ZERO.              
003100                                                                          
003200     05  XML-TXT-LENGTH          PIC 9(03).                               
003300     05  XML-MAX-LINE-LENGTH     PIC 9(03)   VALUE 120.                   
003400     05  XML-WRAP-LENGTH         PIC 9(03)   VALUE  74.                   
003500     05  XML-ATTR-BUFFER         PIC X(80)   VALUE SPACES.                
003600     05  XML-ATTR-POS            PIC 9(03)   VALUE 1.                     
003700                                                                          
003800 01  XML-FORMAT-ABEND-CODE       PIC S9(04)  VALUE +0                     
003900                                             COMP SYNC.                   
